name: GKSessionError.Code
desc: Error codes for the GKSession error domain.

items.name: case invalidParameterError
items.desc: A parameter had an unexpected value.

items.name: case peerNotFoundError
items.desc: A peer with the specified peerID string could not be found.

items.name: case declinedError
items.desc: The peer your application tried to connect to refused the connection.

items.name: case timedOutError
items.desc: The operation could not be completed in the specified timeout period.

items.name: case cancelledError
items.desc: A peer that invited the session to connect to them canceled the connection request.

items.name: case connectionFailedError
items.desc: The attempt to establish a connection with another peer failed.

items.name: case connectionClosedError
items.desc: The connection to another peer closed unexpectedly.

items.name: case dataTooBigError
items.desc: The data your application attempted to send was too large for the session to transmit in a single call.

items.name: case inProgressError
items.desc: The peer your application attempted to connect to has already requested a connection to your session.

items.name: case connectivityError
items.desc: An error occurred in the GKSession object's connection code.

items.name: case transportError
items.desc: An error occurred in the GKSession object's transport code.

items.name: case internalError
items.desc: A serious error occurred inside GKSession.

items.name: case unknownError
items.desc: Reserved for when the error does not fit in another category above.

items.name: case systemError
items.desc: An error occurred outside of the GKSession object's control, such as memory allocation.
